        followup: "Then came the sham surgery trials. Patients were randomized to real arthroscopy or fake surgery (incisions but no actual procedure). The result: <strong>no difference</strong>. Patients improved equally whether they received real surgery or placebo. Decades of certainty, billions of dollars, millions of surgeries—all based on the placebo effect that surgeons couldn't see. The certainty had been based on uncontrolled observations. Controlled trials revealed the truth."
