        followup: "By 2010, meta-analyses showed: consistent HbA1c improvement (~0.3%), reduced severe hypoglycemia, improved quality of life. <strong>Risk of bias:</strong> Some concerns but improving over time. <strong>Inconsistency:</strong> Low for HbA1c, moderate for hypoglycemia (likely explainable by patient selection). <strong>Indirectness:</strong> None—direct outcomes in target population. <strong>Imprecision:</strong> Resolved with cumulative trials. <strong>Publication bias:</strong> Low concern with trials in multiple settings. Final rating: <strong>MODERATE to HIGH</strong> for HbA1c improvement, with appropriate nuance for other outcomes."
